Personally,  I was thankful for the original post and did check out the
sit=
e..  But I could have done without all the bickering it caused.  One post
t=
hat some felt was annoying  has turned into 5 posts that are getting pretty=

darn annoying.  (and now my 2cents makes it six)  wouldn&#39;t simply ignoring=

or deleting the original posting been easier on everyone?



-----Origina=
l Message-----
From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@...=
m] On Behalf Of
Early Cuyler
Sent: Wednesday, December 03, 2008 3:43 PM
To:=
 EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nominees =
Site is now OPEN!



Rejecting spam is absolutely your right. It is also t=
he right of others to
post what they choose as long as it is within the gui=
delines of the groups
moderator of which you are not. 

As far as my making=
 the distinction, the headline of the post was clear as
to the contents, so=
 therefore, you chose to read it. Now if someone was
there holding you agai=
nst your will until you read it, then I apologize.

Jeremy





  _____  

=
From: Clara Febach &lt;cfebach@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: We=
dnesday, December 3, 2008 4:05:14 PM
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Offici=
al Nominees Site is now OPEN!


Dear Jeremy,



The length of membership i=
s not an issue for me. Someone who is a part of
this group for a longer len=
gth has no more rights than a newbie. I joined
EVP-ITC not IPAA.  If I read=
 messages sent from EVP-ITC I expect stuff
related to that group ONLY.  If =
I join IPAA and read messages sent from IPAA
then I expect stuff related to=
 that group ONLY as well.



If the message is sent by EVP-ITC and I open =
it and it is about something
else entirely under the assumption it was abou=
t EVP-ITC, I WAS MADE TO READ
IT. I&#39;m sorry you cannot make that distinctio=
n.



There is a difference between mentioning something off handedly vs. =
running
an entire ad. I do have the right to reject spam.



The moderator=
 did reply to me and that was sufficient. Thank you very much.



~Clara

=
--- On Tue, 12/2/08, Early Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@yahoo. com&gt; wrote:

From: Early =
Cuyler &lt;ecuyler@yahoo. com&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nomine=
es Site is now OPEN!
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
Date: Tuesday, December 2=
, 2008, 1:29 PM

The IPAA is run by people who have been members for a long=
 time. It is
paranormal related and fine by me. No I&#39;m not a member of IPAA=
, but they
have a right to post if they like as long as it does not break t=
he rules.
Nobody is making you read the posts and you don&#39;t have to click a=
nything you
don&#39;t want to.

Jeremy 




  _____  


From: Clara Febach &lt;cf=
ebach@yahoo. com&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
Sent: Tuesday, December 2, 2=
008 2:49:50 PM
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nominees Site is no=
w OPEN!


Who is IPAA and why am I receiving this information with a link f=
or me to
click on?



I would prefer not to receive these kinds of invitat=
ions through this group.
I usually get enough ads as it is without getting =
them enclosed in messages
from groups I belong to. In the past I have recei=
ved invitations sent
directly to my email address and read them when it is =
convenient for me to
take EXTRA time to read them.



Please don&#39;t make me=
 hesitate to open EVP-ITC messages.



Thank you.


--- On Tue, 12/2/08, g=
huny1 &lt;itcnap@gmail. com&gt; wrote:

From: ghuny1 &lt;itcnap@gmail. com&gt;
Subject:=
 [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nominees Site is now OPEN!
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogr=
oups .com
Date: Tuesday, December 2, 2008, 10:27 AM

Dear Friends,

Welcome=
 to the Official IPAA Nominations site. This is a new venture
and has never=
 been done before on this global level. This site, ANYONE
can join, it is F=
REE, you can showcase your work, network with others,
create projects with =
new friends, and of course showcase your sincere
dedicated hard work, promo=
te yourselves, and promote your books,
movies, music, TV shows, radio shows=
, all your talent in the
Paranormal! Networking and helping others in a hau=
nting or a Mufon
watch, the ideas are endless!

We are working hard to find=
 sponsorships and unfortunately this 1st
annual event, donations are requir=
ed to help offset the awards. Any
donations at $25.00 or more would be grea=
tly appreciated.

All nominees, will become featured members. The donations=
 are good
till Nov 7, 2009 and that&#39;s a wonderful savings and very affordab=
le
for all to participate and enjoy ALL YOUR hard work!

Sending You All th=
e Best from IPAA

http://www.ipaaward &lt;http://www.ipaawards.org/&gt;  s.org

L=
aura Kimberley,
Director of IPAA












